1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Kelly's mother-in-law visits for the weekend, while Jenna helps Rachel deal with the news that she didn't get pregnant, yet again. Mags decides to date for the first time since her divorce.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: Jenna learns not to take her husband for granted while Rachel overextends herself again, and throws a huge house-warming party, furthering her own stress. Kelly helps Mags regain her footing in the dating world after several failed first blind dates.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Kelly cleans house to impress her mother-in-law and ends up liking the result. Mags resolves to be a single cat-lady the rest of her life until Rachel introduces her to on-line dating. Rachel baby-sits Jenna's wild toddler and almost compromises a huge e-commerce account doing so.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Mags goes on a series of web-dates and decides to give her love life up to fate, but give herself a makeover. Kelly goes on an organizing rampage to further impress her mother-in-law. Jenna helps her realize she's been trying to hold onto her kids' childhoods but holding onto their stuff. Rachel gets a killer job offer, considers it.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: Mags, made-over, meets a hunky fireman. Rachel decides to decline her job offer and concentrate on "relaxing." Jenna gets neurotic about a contagious cold and Rachel helps her calm down.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Mags runs into her ex-husband with her new fireman-boyfriend. Jenna freaks out when her twins stop kicking. Rachel plans a weekend away. Kelly becomes a clean-freak vigilante and makes her family miserable.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Mags and the fireman break up. Kelly and her mother-in-law finally fight. Jenna's husband accepts a business trip right when she is due to have the twins. Rachel closes down a few of her many, many projects, and truly learns to relax.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: Mags gets in touch with a high-school sweetheart. Kelly finds new ground with her mother-in-law. Rachel discovers she's pregnant. Jenna gives birth to two beautiful babies, and realize one has Super Powers.

imdb.plot outline: At the end of a cul-de-sac, somewhere in suburban California, live four women. Four very different women. At different ages and stages in their lives, from different socio-economic backgrounds, with different marital and parenting statuses, in different "shapes and sizes." But one thing UNITES them: When they're not cleaning house, driving carpool, cooking and/or conference-calling for their careers -- these four women are - Super Heroes. That's right. They work, take care of their families, clean up their homes - and make the world safe from evil. These women are SUPERMOMS.
